        "question_DpKjjK": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "How should I care for my Bib Tights?",
            "content": "<p>The sooner the better; wash your gear soon after wearing to avoid the fabric breaking down from the enzymes in sweat.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_bUAFXw": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What is the difference between lightweight and thermal tights?",
            "content": "<p>The lightweight tights use the same fabric weight as our Summer Bib Shorts. They are great for cool mornings, chilly rides, and offer UV protection. The Thermal Tights are made with a brushed fleece fabric that keeps you warm while also breathing when the gradient rises or when you're racing your friend to the coffee shop. They both have the same fit, and both have pockets.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_QUPKM6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "What is DWR?",
            "content": "<p>DWR stands for Durable Water Repellent, a fabric treatment that helps water bead up and roll off instead of soaking in. We use a C0 DWR, which is a PFAS free alternative that avoids harmful forever chemicals while still shedding road spray and light rain, better for you, better for the places we ride.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
            "icon_size": 20,
            "icon_color": ""
          }
        },
        "question_NXRDD9": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "default_open": false,
            "title": "Are these tights PFAS free?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. These tights use a C0 DWR treatment, meaning they are PFAS free and do not rely on harmful forever chemicals. It is a more responsible way to stay dry, without cutting corners on performance.</p>",
            "show_icon": false,
            "icon_name": "icon-award",
